data.title: Arnold Schwarzenegger's family supports him at 'FUBAR' red carpet premiere
data.meta_description: Arnold Schwarzenegger was joined by three of his children at the red carpet premiere of his new series "FUBAR."
data.text:
Arnold Schwarzenegger's red carpet premiere for his new series "FUBAR" turned into a mini family reunion.

The 75-year-old "Terminator" star was joined by daughters Katherine Schwarzenegger, 33, and Christina Schwarzenegger, 31, at the star-studded event on May 22 at AMC's The Grove theater in Los Angeles.

Marvel star Chris Pratt, who is married to and shares two daughters with Katherine Schwarzenegger, also showed up to support his action star father-in-law.

Arnold Schwarzenegger shares his two daughters -- as well as sons Patrick Schwarzenegger, 29, and Christopher Schwarzenegger, 25 -- with ex-wife Maria Shriver.

Also in attendance was Joseph Baena, the former California governor's son with Mildred Baena. Joseph Baena, who competed on season 31 of "Dancing with the Stars," walked the carpet solo on Monday night.

According to the series description, "FUBAR" stars Arnold Schwarzenegger as Luke Brunner, a CIA operative who is forced to put his retirement on hold and take one last job after discovering a big family secret.

The show also stars Monica Barbaro, Milan Carter, Fortune Feimster and Travis Van Winkle, among others.

"FUBAR" begins streaming May 25 on Netflix.
